    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Charleston</placeName>
                <date>May 15 1855</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev I Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Pa.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Dr Sir. I have<lb/> delayed writing you for some weeks in the<lb/>
                hope that I might send you a remittance<lb/> at the same time, but I have been
                much<lb/> disappointed in making collections. <persName>Charles<lb/> Levy</persName>
                says he has not received the Occident<lb/> &amp; is unwilling to pay for it.
                    <persName>Col Jacobs</persName> obj<lb/>-ects to the Bible because not well
                enough<lb/> bound for the price, &amp; <persName>B D Lazarus</persName>
                declares<lb/> that he will not pay for the Bible without<lb/> a Law Suit because in
                a letter to you wri<lb/>-tten before it was published he requested<lb/> you to
                cancel his subscription. <persName>Mr Hart</persName> tells<lb/> me that
                    <persName>David Seixas</persName> has taken &amp; I presume<lb/> paid for his
                    <sic>sett</sic> of Prayer Books. I shall<lb/> not relinquish in despair the
                collection<lb/> of the Bills you left with me, but will<lb/> urge payment
                energetically &amp; hope soon<lb/> to write you a more favorable report.<lb/> Mother
                is in <placeName>Sumterville</placeName> spending some<lb/> weeks very agreeably.
                All well at home.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">With high regard.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Believe me Yrs truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">Thos. J Moise</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
